This paper presents a model for answering questions about the content of an image, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the model uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper evaluates the model's performance using a Turing Test, which involves human evaluation, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category as well.
